The paper discusses a new algorithm for event detection from complex data streams in syndromic surveillance. The algorithm uses eigenspace techniques to track changes in data correlation structure. This methodology falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG), as it involves developing algorithms that can learn from data. The paper also discusses the statistical significance of the detected events, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). The use of multivariate and seasonal data with spatial and temporal dimensions suggests that the paper may also fall under the categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper involves the analysis of large datasets, which suggests that it may also fall under the category of data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
